cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC 

This paper deals with the delay in a wireless network, which is a common topic in the networking community. The use of micro-energy harvesting is a specific aspect of wireless networks, which suggests the paper could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with energy uncertainty and complex network topology, which could suggest it belongs to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of theoretical analysis and simulations suggests it could belong to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
